      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">The Story</h2>
      <p>I didn't start as an "assistant." I started inside operations — onboarding and training agents on BPO floors in Nairobi, where reliability isn't a value statement, it's a contractual SLA with penalties. That environment teaches you the two skills this work actually runs on: building systems that hold under volume, and communicating status so clearly that nobody has to ask.</p>
      <p>From there the work widened: coordinating a fintech's market expansion out of Stockholm, running stakeholder communication between a CEO and program partners at an international NGO, managing a service transition for a BPO chief executive, coordinating partnerships across African markets. Somewhere along the way I noticed the pattern: every founder I worked with needed the same three things — their time back, an execution rhythm, and systems that don't depend on heroics. Different job titles, same job.</p>
      <p>That's why this site lists <a href="/hire-me/">eleven role names</a>. Companies search for the title their org chart uses. The work underneath is one craft.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">How I Work</h2>
      <p>Three principles, visible in every engagement. <strong>Visibility:</strong> every commitment tracked, every owner named — dashboards replace inbox archaeology. <strong>Discipline:</strong> SLAs on response time, decisions logged, prep delivered 24 hours ahead. <strong>Async-first:</strong> documented processes and decision-ready summaries built for multi-time-zone teams. The full methodology is on <a href="/services/">the services page</a>; the receipts are in <a href="/case-studies/">the case studies</a> and <a href="/portfolio/">portfolio</a>.</p>

